laazotea.indi.driver

Class INDISwitchOneOrNoneProperty

  • java.lang.Object
    • laazotea.indi.driver.INDIProperty
      • laazotea.indi.driver.INDISwitchProperty
        • laazotea.indi.driver.INDISwitchOneOrNoneProperty
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class INDISwitchOneOrNoneProperty
extends INDISwitchProperty
    A class representing a INDI One or None Switch Property (aka a simple button). It simplifies dealing with Switch elements and so on.
    Version:
    1.34, January 11, 2014
    Author:
    S. Alonso (Zerjillo) [zerjioi at ugr.es]
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

                                                                         throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Loads an instance of INDISwitchOneOrNoneProperty from a file or, if it cannot be loaded, constructs it with a particular driver, name, label, group, state, permission, timeout, option and initialStatus. The property will autosave its status to a file every time that it is changed.
        Parameters:
        driver - The Driver to which this property is associated.
        name - The name of the Property
        label - The label of the Property
        group - The group of the Property
        state - The initial state of the Property
        permission - The permission of the Property
        timeout - The timeout of the Property
        option - The name of the option
        initialStatus - The initial status of the option
        Returns:
        The loaded switch one or none property or a new constructed one if cannot be loaded.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        See Also:
        INDISwitchProperty

      • getStatus

        public laazotea.indi.Constants.SwitchStatus getStatus(INDISwitchElementAndValue[] ev)
        Gets the status of the Element of the Property that would be set according to some pairs of ev and values. This method DOES NOT change the status of the Element NOR it gives the actual status of it.
        Parameters:
        ev - The pairs of ev and values (only one except some error / strange behaviour).
        Returns:
        The status of the Element of the Property that would be set
